    "permit_type": "Electrical PermitOne or Two Family Dwelling/StructureAddition/Alteration/Replacement",
    "work_description": "(1) string of PV Arrays shall be installed on the detached structure in order to maximize production values. In order to run the PV circuit wiring from the detached structure AC Disconnect to the Combiner Panel location on the north side of the house, we will need to install (2) RMC service masts -- one on the west wall of the detached structure at the Southwest corner, and one on the north facing wall of the main structure, approximately about 10ft apart. - and run Overhead Triplex cable between the masts to the respective electrical box that the masts will be connected to.The mast on the main structure will lead to a PVC junction box where we will need to run exterior conduit from the service mast to the combiner panel just below the service mast on the main structure. Service masts will need to be secured to the walls with a piece of shallow slotted unistrut and a unistrut conduit strap once every 10 ft. length, and will need to extend above their respective roof surface through the eaves approximately 3 ft. Install a roof boot with composite shingle flashing for each service mast to prevent water leakage. We will maintain 3' clearance around the service masts on the roof surfaces. When the overhead cable is ran between the masts, the lowest point of the cable will need to be a minimum of 12' above grade level. Service Mast will connect into the AC Disconnect through a UL listed hub sized for the conduit size, and the PVC junction box through a Myers Hub. AC Disconnect will need to be a 60A rated unit due to the size of the overhead triplex cable, which has a minimum size of #6 AWG. Drive (2) ground rods for the AC Disconnect on the detached structure and run a #6 AWG Solid Bare GEC wire.",
